=== Part Three — Sharing of Preparations Within Community Contexts

The absolute prohibition on sharing preparations stated in Safety Document E.4 applies with equal force within community contexts. No Gathering, peer connection, Guide relationship, or community event creates any exception.

#safety[
  No student may share, give, sell, barter, or transfer any self-produced preparation to any other student, Guide, or Academy affiliate, whether in person, by post, or by any other means. No Guide, Headmaster, or Academy affiliate will accept any preparation from any student. Any offer to do so must be declined immediately and reported to the Headmaster.
]

#risk-item(
  "legal liability under federal and Oregon food and drug regulations, civil liability for third-party harm, and administrative removal from the Academy",
  "transferring any self-produced preparation to any person through any community channel or context"
)

=== Part Four — Use of Academy Education Externally

As students advance through Year Three, questions naturally arise about engaging with the broader alchemical community. The following principles apply:

*Attribution:* Ideas, methods, or frameworks derived from this curriculum shared externally should be attributed to their source, not represented as the student's original synthesis.

*Accuracy:* Students represent the tradition honestly — including its uncertainties, historical disputes, and the experimental nature of their own practical results.

*No Academy representation:* Completion of the three-year programme qualifies the student within their own practice. It does not create any franchise, teaching licence, or representative status on behalf of the Academy. The Academy does not authorise students to teach or represent this curriculum on its behalf.

=== Part Five — Termination of Academy Oversight

*The Academy's duty of care toward the student formally and fully terminates upon the student's completion of Year Three, Month Twelve.*

Upon signing and submitting the Declaration of Completion (Year Three Month 12, Week 4), the following is affirmed:

- The student's participation in the formal TTAO Inner Academy programme has concluded.
- The Academy's educational oversight, Guide relationship, and all associated support structures have concluded.
- The Academy's duty of care — to the extent any such duty existed within the educational relationship — is fully discharged.
- The student enters the post-curriculum phase as an independent practitioner, bearing full and sole responsibility for any alchemical work undertaken thereafter.

The Academy retains no ongoing responsibility for, and disclaims all liability arising from, any alchemical work, use of preparations, teaching, or other activity the student undertakes after programme completion. This termination of oversight applies regardless of whether the student continues alchemical work, continues to use curriculum methods, or seeks informal contact with Guides or Academy affiliates after completion.

Post-completion contact with the Academy is welcomed as collegial exchange and carries no implication of renewed duty of care, mentorship, or safety oversight.

=== Part Six — Amendment and Removal

The Academy reserves the right to amend this agreement. Students will be notified of material changes.

The Academy reserves the right to administratively remove any student who:
- Shares or transfers preparations to any person
- Misrepresents their work, identity, or qualifications within the community
- Violates any term of any Academy Safety Document
- Engages in harassment, coercion, or manipulation of any Academy participant

Removal decisions are made by the Headmaster and are final.

